				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I read in an interview in an old magazine (Super Power) during the SNES era where Miyamoto clearly said that he gave Mario a cap because he wasn't confident in drawing hair. It sounded like the cap was a design decision to make things easier for himself. Although it wasn't clear if he was talking about the concept art or the sprite graphics (the interview came with pictures of early concept art which made me initially interpret it as it was about the concept art). I guess this eventually somehow turned into the &quot;hardware didn't allow animated hair&quot; misinterpretation which is of course either BS or badly phrased sentences.<br /><br />The moustache and overalls are probably about the sprite graphics though as it possibly made him stand out more with such limited resolution. So I think it could be said it's about techniques to make art despite the hardware constraints, rather than incapable hardware.</div>

